text: Tinne Gilis (born 29 October 1997 in Mol) is a Belgian professional squash player. As of January 2020, she was ranked number 22 in the world. ==Personal life== Tinne's older sister, Nele Gilis is also a squash player and her fellow competitor on the PSA World Tour. Her younger brother Jo Gilis is a professional footballer in Belgium who has represented the Belgian national under-16 and under-17 football teams. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Belgian female squash players
